    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawings or works in another two-dimensional medium representing one longitudinal half of a ship as viewed from above and emphasizing the ship's lines. When appearing with a body plan and a sheer plan, use "lines drawings" for the set.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000013911/McEwen and Lewis, Encyclopedia of Nautical Knowledge (1953)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dibujos que representan una mitad longitudinal de un barco, como visto desde arriba y enfatizando las líneas del barco. Cuando aparece con un plano de casco y un plano longitudinal, use "dibujo de líneas" para el conjunto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tekeningen van lengtedoorsnede van een schip, van boven gezien, en met nadruk op de lijnen van het schip. Gebruik 'lijnentekeningen' als daar ook een plattegrond van de romp en een zeegplan bijkomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052542/Bibliotheek Scheepvaartmuseum (z.j.)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以俯視的角度呈現船體縱線的製圖或平面作品，強調船體的線條。若與船體橫剖面線圖及船體縱剖面線圖同時出現，則使用「船體線型圖」一詞指稱整組圖則。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Desenhos ou trabalhos em outros meios bidimensionais que representam uma metade longitudinal de uma embarcação conforme vista de cima e que enfatiza suas linhas. Quando aparecem com um plano de baliza e um plano de perfil, use "desenhos de linhas" para o conjunto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
